Male. Color (in 80 % ethanol). Body creamy, with brown spots as indicated below. Head pattern (
Fig. 65
), with longitudinal creamy bands from each compound eye to clypeus, limited on outer borders by ochre genae, and on inner borders by ochre striae of postclypeus, and by dark brown areas on sides of ocellar group, as illustrated. Compound eyes black, ocelli hyaline, with ochre centripetal crescents; labrum dark brown, creamy on sides. Maxillary palps pale brown, Mx 4 brown. Antennae brown, scape and pedicel dark brown. Thorax brown, meso- and metapleura with large, dark brown spots. Coxae dark brown, mid and hind coxae with small, brown areas, femora proximally dark brown, tibiae brown. Forewings (
Fig. 63
), hyaline, pterostigma with proximal and distal dark brown bands, a submarginal brown band from R 4 + 5 to areola postica, and a large brown area distally in cells Cu 1 and Cu 2 , as illustrated; brown areola on veins in setae insertions, and dark brown spots distally on veins, at wing margin. Abdomen yellowish brown, with dark brown subcuticular bands. Hypandrium brown, darker anteriorly; epiproct and paraprocts pale brown. Phallosome brown, with endophallic sclerites dark brown.

Morphology. As in diagnosis, plus the following: Head: H/MxW: 1.42 ; compound eyes large, H/d: 2.57 ; IO/ MxW: 0.76 . Outer cusp of lacinial tip broad, with four denticles. Mx 4 /Mx 2 : 1.4 . Forewings (
Fig. 63
): L/W: 3.61 ; M 5 -branched, M 5 distally forked. Pterostigma: lp/wp: 3.92 , areola postica tall, triangular: al/ah: 1.41 . Hindwings (
Fig. 64
): l/w: 2.80 . Hypandrium (
Fig. 67
), of one sclerite, setose as illustrated; phallosome (
Fig. 68
) with external parameres dilated distally, apically rounded, the outer border with a row of denticles. Two pairs of endophallic sclerites, anterior pair each with a straight, acuminate central piece, joined proximally to a curved broad piece, distally acuminate, directed inwards; posterior pair long, slender, with apex bearing two acuminate projections, the inner one curved inwards. Epiproct (
Fig. 66
) wide, convex anteriorly, rounded posteriorly, with setae as illustrated. Paraprocts (
Fig. 66
), broad, with a macrosetae near sensory field, and a distal setal field; sensory fields with 25 trichobothria on basal rosettes.

